  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "1.     Number of staff with knowledge and skills in Nutrition in Emergencies, health in emergencies  and  HIV AIDS in emergency available in  Health sector\r\n2.     Strategic framework to respond to the health and nutritional needs (based on CCC and sphere standards) of at least 50% children and pregnant and lactating women in emergencies available by 2011 and outlined activities  implemented in 2012 in all humanitarian crisis \r\n \r\n3.     Number of disaster prone districts with operational District Contingency Plan (DCP) including health and nutrition component that incorporates gender and equity issues in line with CCCs.\r\n4.   Stockpiles of emergency health and nutrition  supplies available for 50,000 affected population  including appropriate health and nutrition supplies for women and adolescence girls at strategic locations (Biratnagar for East, Bharatpur for Central and West, Nepalgung for Mid and Far West region"
    },
    "ne": null
